You are an AI coding agent working on the Paperboyy project.

High priority rules (must follow)
- Do not use emojis in any output (chat or code).
- This project uses Express + EJS. Do not create .html pages for app routes. Use routes like /browser, /search, /paper/:paperId.
- Keep OCR out of scope. Do not implement any OCR pipeline unless explicitly requested later.
- Use Tailwind styling that matches the high-contrast modernist engineering-grid design in extras/DESIGN.md and extras/code.html.

Comments in every file
- Every new or edited source file must start with a short top-of-file comment explaining what the file is responsible for.
  - JavaScript/TypeScript: use // at the top.
  - EJS: use <%# ... %> at the top.
  - CSS: use /* ... */ at the top.
  - JSON: do not add comments (JSON does not allow them). Instead, keep intent in README or adjacent docs.
- Comments must explain intent and responsibilities, not narrate obvious code.

Architecture constraints
- Use server-rendered EJS pages with partials. Do not duplicate boilerplate across pages.
- Split view boilerplate into EJS partials at minimum:
  - views/layouts/base.ejs
  - views/partials/head.ejs
  - views/partials/navbar.ejs
  - views/partials/footer.ejs
  - views/partials/scripts.ejs (Vite dev/prod loader)
- Keep page routes and API routes separate (e.g., src/routes/pages/* and src/routes/api/*).
- Keep business logic out of route files; route files should call controllers/services.

Error handling (required)
- No unhandled promise rejections.
- Every async route handler must be wrapped (e.g., asyncHandler(fn)).
- Centralize error handling middleware:
  - Render custom EJS pages for 404 and 500.
  - For /api/* routes, return JSON errors in a consistent shape:
    {
      error: { code: string, message: string, requestId: string }
    }
- Never leak secrets or stack traces to the client in production.

Auth + authorization
- Use Clerk for authentication.
- Protect signed-in pages (e.g., /dashboard, /upload) with auth middleware.
- Admin pages and admin APIs must be protected by an admin guard (admin identity via env-configured Clerk user id).

Core product scope reminders
- Upload flow is Submission -> Admin Inbox -> Admin converts to Paper/Questions/Answers.
- Suggested content must stay simple (or omit it) to avoid complexity.

Code quality
- Prefer small modules with clear responsibilities.
- Validate inputs at the edges (routes/controllers). Return user-friendly errors.
- Use consistent naming and folder structure aligned to extras/PAPERBOYY_MASTERPLAN.md.

